00:53:43.080 --> 00:53:48.440
[Amit Varma]: I spoke about how about Milton Friedman's famous warning about how pro markets and pro

00:53:48.440 --> 00:53:53.000
[Amit Varma]: business are two opposite things almost, you know, the exact point you were making, you

00:53:53.000 --> 00:53:57.120
[Amit Varma]: know, citing Rajan's book, Saving Capitalists from the Capitalists. And I would argue then

00:53:57.120 --> 00:54:01.560
[Amit Varma]: that I have a mild objection to your phrase about inequality capturing the state, I think

00:54:01.560 --> 00:54:05.840
[Amit Varma]: the rich capture the state. And the problem there with the rich capturing the state is

00:54:05.840 --> 00:54:08.940
[Amit Varma]: that why are they capturing the state, they're capturing the state because the state has

00:54:08.940 --> 00:54:13.460
[Amit Varma]: much more power than it should. And therefore, they can generate more money for themselves.

00:54:13.460 --> 00:54:16.720
[Amit Varma]: And this is a very perverse process. And I agree with you that it harms the poor the

00:54:16.720 --> 00:54:23.400
[Amit Varma]: most and allows the rich to generate more wealth for themselves through state coercion.

00:54:23.400 --> 00:54:27.880
[Amit Varma]: And the solution there is not to outlaw the rich. But the solution there I would say is

00:54:27.880 --> 00:54:32.560
[Amit Varma]: to reduce the power of the state. So the rich don't want to capture the state because there's

00:54:32.560 --> 00:54:36.080
[Amit Varma]: nothing in it for them. The only way they can make more money is, you know, through

00:54:36.080 --> 00:54:41.080
[Amit Varma]: the pursuit of profit and adding value to the lives of other people. On that note, you

