02:09:34.560 --> 02:09:35.560
[Amit Varma]: Welcome back once again to the

02:09:35.560 --> 02:09:36.560
[Amit Varma]: Seen and the Unseen.

02:09:36.560 --> 02:09:38.560
[Amit Varma]: I'm chatting with Karthik Mudlidharan

02:09:38.560 --> 02:09:40.560
[Amit Varma]: about the state of Indian education.

02:09:40.560 --> 02:09:42.560
[Amit Varma]: And it's about time we actually get down

02:09:42.560 --> 02:09:44.560
[Amit Varma]: to concrete brass tacks and talk about

02:09:44.560 --> 02:09:47.560
[Amit Varma]: how we could actually improve the state

02:09:47.560 --> 02:09:48.560
[Amit Varma]: of our public schools.

02:09:48.560 --> 02:09:51.560
[Amit Varma]: And reading Karthik's many papers and

02:09:51.560 --> 02:09:53.560
[Amit Varma]: watching his interviews and all of that,

02:09:53.560 --> 02:09:55.560
[Amit Varma]: I've always come away with so much

02:09:55.560 --> 02:09:57.560
[Amit Varma]: insight into what the problem is.

02:09:57.560 --> 02:09:58.560
[Amit Varma]: So Karthik, go ahead.

02:09:58.560 --> 02:10:00.560
[Amit Varma]: What are the sort of things that,

02:10:00.560 --> 02:10:01.560
[Amit Varma]: if you had unlimited power,

02:10:01.560 --> 02:10:03.560
[Amit Varma]: if there was no democracy and you were

02:10:03.560 --> 02:10:05.560
[Guest]: the man in charge, what would you do?

02:10:05.560 --> 02:10:06.560
[Guest]: So let me first of all say,

02:10:06.560 --> 02:10:07.560
[Guest]: I want democracy.

02:10:07.560 --> 02:10:09.560
[Guest]: And in fact, I'll tell you what I would

02:10:09.560 --> 02:10:11.560
[Guest]: do if I was in charge.

02:10:11.560 --> 02:10:13.560
[Guest]: But certainly there's an aspect of this

02:10:13.560 --> 02:10:15.560
[Guest]: that, and let me take a step back

02:10:15.560 --> 02:10:17.560
[Guest]: and talk about the power of good data

02:10:17.560 --> 02:10:19.560
[Guest]: and the power of good ideas.

02:10:19.560 --> 02:10:21.560
[Guest]: And in my interactions with Kaushik Basu,

02:10:21.560 --> 02:10:22.560
[Guest]: Arvind Subramaniam, and again,

02:10:22.560 --> 02:10:23.560
[Guest]: they would say this again and again,

02:10:23.560 --> 02:10:25.560
[Guest]: is that, you know, your typical

02:10:25.560 --> 02:10:28.560
[Guest]: policymaker is just, it's so easy

02:10:28.560 --> 02:10:30.560
[Guest]: to criticize the bureaucrat, right?

02:10:30.560 --> 02:10:32.560
[Guest]: But if you spend a day observing

02:10:32.560 --> 02:10:34.560
[Guest]: their lives, I mean, it is not a life

02:10:34.560 --> 02:10:37.560
[Guest]: anybody would want in terms of the sheer

02:10:37.560 --> 02:10:39.560
[Guest]: pressures that they're under in terms of,

02:10:39.560 --> 02:10:41.560
[Guest]: you know, the almost inhuman number of

02:10:41.560 --> 02:10:42.560
[Guest]: things that have to be delivered

02:10:42.560 --> 02:10:43.560
[Guest]: in a time-bound way, okay?

02:10:43.560 --> 02:10:46.560
[Guest]: So, and they just, even the best of them,

02:10:46.560 --> 02:10:47.560
[Guest]: you know, and as you know,

02:10:47.560 --> 02:10:48.560
[Guest]: the other version of Parkinson's law is

02:10:48.560 --> 02:10:49.560
[Guest]: the only reward for good work

02:10:49.560 --> 02:10:50.560
[Guest]: is more work, right?

02:10:50.560 --> 02:10:52.560
[Guest]: Like, you know, so even when you get

02:10:52.560 --> 02:10:54.560
[Guest]: very good people, they get saddled

02:10:54.560 --> 02:10:56.560
[Guest]: with more and more responsibilities

02:10:56.560 --> 02:10:58.560
[Guest]: till the best, each person has enough

02:10:58.560 --> 02:10:59.560
[Guest]: responsibilities to be close

02:10:59.560 --> 02:11:00.560
[Guest]: to their breaking point, right?

02:11:00.560 --> 02:11:02.560
[Guest]: Like, you know, so which means that

02:11:02.560 --> 02:11:05.560
[Guest]: it's kind of, you know, it's really more

02:11:05.560 --> 02:11:07.560
[Guest]: about not criticizing the bureaucracy,

02:11:07.560 --> 02:11:10.560
[Guest]: but recognizing the incredible constraints

02:11:10.560 --> 02:11:11.560
[Guest]: under which they function.

02:11:11.560 --> 02:11:12.560
[Guest]: And then for those of us, like,

02:11:12.560 --> 02:11:14.560
[Guest]: who have the luxury of time

02:11:14.560 --> 02:11:16.560
[Guest]: to kind of think deeper, harder thoughts

02:11:16.560 --> 02:11:18.560
[Guest]: about what is wrong, and how do you

02:11:18.560 --> 02:11:20.560
[Guest]: then want to improve, you know,

02:11:20.560 --> 02:11:21.560
[Guest]: it's our kind of response,

02:11:21.560 --> 02:11:23.560
[Guest]: because so much, it's just so easy

02:11:23.560 --> 02:11:24.560
[Guest]: to throw stones from the outside,

02:11:24.560 --> 02:11:27.560
[Guest]: that part of our kind of moral responsibility

02:11:27.560 --> 02:11:29.560
[Guest]: as how do we contribute our piece

02:11:29.560 --> 02:11:31.560
[Guest]: of this ecosystem is to just clarify

02:11:31.560 --> 02:11:32.560
[Guest]: the basic facts, right?

02:11:32.560 --> 02:11:34.560
[Guest]: And once you clarify the basic facts,

02:11:34.560 --> 02:11:36.560
[Guest]: then going back to democracy,

02:11:36.560 --> 02:11:37.560
[Guest]: it's like, we think about,

02:11:37.560 --> 02:11:39.560
[Guest]: there's good democracy and bad democracy,

02:11:39.560 --> 02:11:41.560
[Guest]: right? So, there's good politics

02:11:41.560 --> 02:11:42.560
[Guest]: and bad politics.

02:11:42.560 --> 02:11:43.560
[Guest]: The bad part of politics is the pursuit

02:11:43.560 --> 02:11:44.560
[Guest]: of power and keeping power,

02:11:44.560 --> 02:11:46.560
[Guest]: which is unfortunately what most of the

02:11:46.560 --> 02:11:48.560
[Guest]: time the media is focused on.

02:11:48.560 --> 02:11:50.560
[Guest]: There is a good part of politics,

02:11:50.560 --> 02:11:52.560
[Guest]: which is how do you adjudicate conflicting

02:11:52.560 --> 02:11:54.560
[Guest]: claims in society and come up

02:11:54.560 --> 02:11:56.560
[Guest]: with a win-win solution, right?

02:11:56.560 --> 02:11:58.560
[Guest]: So, and I'm very glad you brought up politics,

02:11:58.560 --> 02:11:59.560
[Guest]: because many of the ideas

02:11:59.560 --> 02:12:00.560
[Guest]: I'm going to talk about,

02:12:00.560 --> 02:12:01.560
[Guest]: I'm also going to talk about

02:12:01.560 --> 02:12:03.560
[Guest]: what might be political constraints

02:12:03.560 --> 02:12:04.560
[Guest]: and what would be, you know,

02:12:04.560 --> 02:12:07.560
[Guest]: essentially a sensitive, democratically

02:12:07.560 --> 02:12:09.560
[Guest]: validated way of implementing

02:12:09.560 --> 02:12:10.560
[Guest]: some of these reforms.

02:12:10.560 --> 02:12:11.560
[Guest]: And so, you know, the reason

02:12:11.560 --> 02:12:13.560
[Guest]: I keep coming back multiple times

02:12:13.560 --> 02:12:15.560
[Guest]: to push back at any suggestion somehow

02:12:15.560 --> 02:12:16.560
[Guest]: that like, you know, if you're a czar,

02:12:16.560 --> 02:12:17.560
[Guest]: you'll get things done.

02:12:17.560 --> 02:12:19.560
[Guest]: It is, you know, it's all about making

02:12:19.560 --> 02:12:20.560
[Guest]: democracy work better.

02:12:20.560 --> 02:12:22.560
[Guest]: And one part of making democracy work

02:12:22.560 --> 02:12:24.560
[Guest]: better is just more facts

02:12:24.560 --> 02:12:26.560
[Guest]: and transparency on, you know,

02:12:26.560 --> 02:12:27.560
[Guest]: where the money goes.

02:12:27.560 --> 02:12:29.560
[Guest]: Is it being spent in an effective way?

02:12:29.560 --> 02:12:30.560
[Guest]: Because what you do is you kind of,

02:12:30.560 --> 02:12:32.560
[Guest]: like you said, for good intentions,

02:12:32.560 --> 02:12:34.560
[Guest]: it's like, if I have said something good,

02:12:34.560 --> 02:12:35.560
[Guest]: the problem with the right to education

02:12:35.560 --> 02:12:36.560
[Guest]: is like, it is like, you know,

02:12:36.560 --> 02:12:38.560
[Guest]: it's like the national flag and apple pie.

02:12:38.560 --> 02:12:39.560
[Guest]: I mean, how do you object

02:12:39.560 --> 02:12:40.560
[Guest]: to a right to education?

02:12:40.560 --> 02:12:41.560
[Guest]: You don't, right?

02:12:41.560 --> 02:12:43.560
[Guest]: The problem is that the innards

02:12:43.560 --> 02:12:44.560
[Guest]: of that act are disastrous, right?

02:12:44.560 --> 02:12:46.560
[Guest]: And so you need to then flesh it out

02:12:46.560 --> 02:12:47.560
[Guest]: and saying the problem is not

02:12:47.560 --> 02:12:48.560
[Guest]: a right to education.

02:12:48.560 --> 02:12:50.560
[Guest]: The problem is this provision

02:12:50.560 --> 02:12:51.560
[Guest]: and how misguided it is.

02:12:51.560 --> 02:12:53.560
[Guest]: And so that's a long hard slog, right?

02:12:53.560 --> 02:12:54.560
[Guest]: So anyway, so I think

02:12:54.560 --> 02:12:55.560
[Guest]: with that caveat aside,

02:12:55.560 --> 02:12:56.560
[Guest]: let's come back and talk about,

02:12:56.560 --> 02:12:59.560
[Guest]: so let's say I was a state education minister

02:12:59.560 --> 02:13:00.560
[Guest]: or, you know, an advisor

02:13:00.560 --> 02:13:01.560
[Guest]: to the union education minister

02:13:01.560 --> 02:13:03.560
[Guest]: and trying to set up certain priorities

02:13:03.560 --> 02:13:05.560
[Guest]: for what we need to do as a country

02:13:05.560 --> 02:13:07.560
[Guest]: and how do we actually make it happen?

02:13:07.560 --> 02:13:08.560
[Guest]: Okay, so the first part,

02:13:08.560 --> 02:13:11.560
[Guest]: which I think is very clear

02:13:11.560 --> 02:13:12.560
[Guest]: and it's in the NAP

02:13:12.560 --> 02:13:15.560
[Guest]: is a foundational literacy numeracy mission

02:13:15.560 --> 02:13:16.560
[Guest]: to make sure, right,

02:13:16.560 --> 02:13:18.560
[Guest]: that every child in the next five years,

02:13:18.560 --> 02:13:20.560
[Guest]: that every child in this country

02:13:20.560 --> 02:13:22.560
[Guest]: has functional foundational literacy numeracy

02:13:22.560 --> 02:13:23.560
[Guest]: defined as the point where

02:13:23.560 --> 02:13:25.560
[Guest]: you can read to learn, okay?

02:13:25.560 --> 02:13:27.560
[Guest]: So the first two or three years in school

02:13:27.560 --> 02:13:28.560
[Guest]: is you learn to read,

02:13:28.560 --> 02:13:31.560
[Guest]: but are you able to then read

02:13:31.560 --> 02:13:33.560
[Guest]: to be able to absorb new content, right?

02:13:33.560 --> 02:13:35.560
[Guest]: So that to me is my functional definition

02:13:35.560 --> 02:13:37.560
[Guest]: of foundational literacy, right?

02:13:37.560 --> 02:13:38.560
[Guest]: Are you at the point

02:13:38.560 --> 02:13:39.560
[Guest]: where you can read to learn content?

02:13:39.560 --> 02:13:41.560
[Guest]: Okay, so and that's what primary school

02:13:41.560 --> 02:13:42.560
[Guest]: is supposed to get you to the point of doing

02:13:42.560 --> 02:13:44.560
[Guest]: and we need to deliver that, okay?

02:13:44.560 --> 02:13:45.560
[Guest]: Now, the question then is

02:13:45.560 --> 02:13:46.560
[Guest]: how are you going to deliver that?

02:13:46.560 --> 02:13:48.560
[Guest]: And I think part of the problem is

02:13:48.560 --> 02:13:50.560
[Guest]: because is the lack of coherence

02:13:50.560 --> 02:13:52.560
[Guest]: with regard to goals down the system.

02:13:52.560 --> 02:13:54.560
[Guest]: So if you go spend time with a teacher

02:13:54.560 --> 02:13:56.560
[Guest]: or spend time with a block education officer,

02:13:56.560 --> 02:13:57.560
[Guest]: if you look at the,

02:13:57.560 --> 02:13:58.560
[Guest]: and this is why you need to get into

02:13:58.560 --> 02:14:00.560
[Guest]: the sinews of the state

02:14:00.560 --> 02:14:01.560
[Guest]: and so much of my work

02:14:01.560 --> 02:14:03.560
[Guest]: is kind of the last mile service delivery

02:14:03.560 --> 02:14:04.560
[Guest]: architecture of this country, right,

02:14:04.560 --> 02:14:07.560
[Guest]: is if you go look at what a teacher

02:14:07.560 --> 02:14:08.560
[Guest]: or Anganwadi worker

02:14:08.560 --> 02:14:10.560
[Guest]: is being held accountable for,

02:14:10.560 --> 02:14:11.560
[Guest]: they're mainly held accountable

02:14:11.560 --> 02:14:12.560
[Guest]: for paperwork, okay?

02:14:12.560 --> 02:14:15.560
[Guest]: So when you get a supervisory visit,

02:14:15.560 --> 02:14:16.560
[Guest]: the first thing this person does

02:14:16.560 --> 02:14:18.560
[Guest]: is come and check your registers, right?

02:14:18.560 --> 02:14:19.560
[Guest]: Is the paperwork in order?

02:14:19.560 --> 02:14:20.560
[Guest]: Is your enrollment correct?

02:14:20.560 --> 02:14:21.560
[Guest]: And you know, there is the,

02:14:21.560 --> 02:14:23.560
[Guest]: any sense of learning outcomes

02:14:23.560 --> 02:14:24.560
[Guest]: is non-existent, okay?

02:14:24.560 --> 02:14:25.560
[Guest]: So at best you might have somebody

02:14:25.560 --> 02:14:26.560
[Guest]: you might call a child

02:14:26.560 --> 02:14:27.560
[Guest]: and ask a question or two,

02:14:27.560 --> 02:14:28.560
[Guest]: but that doesn't happen

02:14:28.560 --> 02:14:30.560
[Guest]: with any clarity down the chain

02:14:30.560 --> 02:14:31.560
[Guest]: as to what is it

02:14:31.560 --> 02:14:32.560
[Guest]: that we're trying to achieve, right?

02:14:32.560 --> 02:14:34.560
[Guest]: So the first part of this is just

02:14:34.560 --> 02:14:36.560
[Guest]: coherence and clarity

02:14:36.560 --> 02:14:37.560
[Guest]: as to what foundational literacy

02:14:37.560 --> 02:14:39.560
[Guest]: numeracy means with regard to

02:14:39.560 --> 02:14:42.560
[Guest]: achieving certain absolute standards, right?

02:14:42.560 --> 02:14:43.560
[Guest]: So it's not about marks.

02:14:43.560 --> 02:14:44.560
[Guest]: It's not about ranks.

02:14:44.560 --> 02:14:47.560
[Guest]: It's about if I give you a sheet of paper

02:14:47.560 --> 02:14:48.560
[Guest]: in second grade or I give you a passage,

02:14:48.560 --> 02:14:49.560
[Guest]: are you able to read it

02:14:49.560 --> 02:14:51.560
[Guest]: and answer four questions, right?

02:14:51.560 --> 02:14:52.560
[Guest]: And again, this should not become like,

02:14:52.560 --> 02:14:54.560
[Guest]: have I memorized that paragraph?

02:14:54.560 --> 02:14:55.560
[Guest]: In fact, it's kind of shocking

02:14:55.560 --> 02:14:56.560
[Guest]: coming back to curricular reforms.

02:14:56.560 --> 02:14:57.560
[Guest]: I remember Madhya Pradesh

02:14:57.560 --> 02:14:58.560
[Guest]: once looking at an

02:14:58.560 --> 02:14:59.560
[Guest]: eight standard Hindi exam

02:14:59.560 --> 02:15:00.560
[Guest]: and I looked at this and said,

02:15:00.560 --> 02:15:02.560
[Guest]: boss, I would fail this exam,

02:15:02.560 --> 02:15:03.560
[Guest]: even though like, you know,

02:15:03.560 --> 02:15:04.560
[Guest]: obviously, you know, my Hindi

02:15:04.560 --> 02:15:06.560
[Guest]: is decent enough to certainly pass

02:15:06.560 --> 02:15:07.560
[Guest]: an eight standard exam.

02:15:07.560 --> 02:15:08.560
[Guest]: But it's because that exam

02:15:08.560 --> 02:15:10.560
[Guest]: was essentially about reciting

02:15:10.560 --> 02:15:11.560
[Guest]: verbatim text like, you know,

02:15:11.560 --> 02:15:12.560
[Guest]: that if you have learned

02:15:12.560 --> 02:15:13.560
[Guest]: a kavita by heart,

02:15:13.560 --> 02:15:14.560
[Guest]: then it'll be kavita me kavi ne

02:15:14.560 --> 02:15:16.560
[Guest]: is pangti me kya kaha, right?

02:15:16.560 --> 02:15:17.560
[Guest]: You know, which is,

02:15:17.560 --> 02:15:19.560
[Guest]: what did the poet say in this line,

02:15:19.560 --> 02:15:22.560
[Guest]: which is essentially an act of memorization

02:15:22.560 --> 02:15:24.560
[Guest]: as opposed to in any way

02:15:24.560 --> 02:15:26.560
[Guest]: a test of language or comprehension, right?

02:15:26.560 --> 02:15:28.560
[Guest]: So the first part is just coherence

02:15:28.560 --> 02:15:30.560
[Guest]: on the assessments and measurement

02:15:30.560 --> 02:15:32.560
[Guest]: so that everybody down the chain

02:15:32.560 --> 02:15:34.560
[Guest]: from the education minister

02:15:34.560 --> 02:15:35.560
[Guest]: to the education secretary

02:15:35.560 --> 02:15:36.560
[Guest]: to the district education officer,

02:15:36.560 --> 02:15:37.560
[Guest]: block education officer, teacher,

02:15:37.560 --> 02:15:39.560
[Guest]: and parent understands

02:15:39.560 --> 02:15:41.560
[Guest]: that as an education system,

02:15:41.560 --> 02:15:42.560
[Guest]: our goal is going to be

02:15:42.560 --> 02:15:44.560
[Guest]: to deliver every child

02:15:44.560 --> 02:15:45.560
[Guest]: reaching these levels, okay?

02:15:45.560 --> 02:15:47.560
[Guest]: And once you have that,

02:15:47.560 --> 02:15:48.560
[Guest]: then there's the question of,

02:15:48.560 --> 02:15:51.560
[Guest]: so it's not just enough to measure, right?

02:15:51.560 --> 02:15:53.560
[Guest]: Because you have this foundational problem

02:15:53.560 --> 02:15:54.560
[Guest]: of data integrity, okay?

02:15:54.560 --> 02:15:56.560
[Guest]: And so it's not like,

02:15:56.560 --> 02:15:57.560
[Guest]: and in fact,

02:15:57.560 --> 02:15:58.560
[Guest]: some of the better initiatives

02:15:58.560 --> 02:15:59.560
[Guest]: in the country, Gujarat,

02:15:59.560 --> 02:16:01.560
[Guest]: again, when the PM was a CM,

02:16:01.560 --> 02:16:02.560
[Guest]: and, you know, I think

02:16:02.560 --> 02:16:03.560
[Guest]: there were many effective things

02:16:03.560 --> 02:16:04.560
[Guest]: he had tried as chief minister,

02:16:04.560 --> 02:16:06.560
[Guest]: including Grunotsav,

02:16:06.560 --> 02:16:07.560
[Guest]: which was his attempt

02:16:07.560 --> 02:16:08.560
[Guest]: to do a universal

02:16:08.560 --> 02:16:09.560
[Guest]: kind of census of learning

02:16:09.560 --> 02:16:10.560
[Guest]: where senior officials would go

02:16:10.560 --> 02:16:11.560
[Guest]: and, you know,

02:16:11.560 --> 02:16:12.560
[Guest]: do this measurement exercise.

02:16:12.560 --> 02:16:14.560
[Guest]: And then Madhya Pradesh, in fact,

02:16:14.560 --> 02:16:15.560
[Guest]: expanded this to what's called

02:16:15.560 --> 02:16:16.560
[Guest]: Pratibha Parv,

02:16:16.560 --> 02:16:17.560
[Guest]: which is a,

02:16:17.560 --> 02:16:18.560
[Guest]: and on paper,

02:16:18.560 --> 02:16:19.560
[Guest]: it's a fantastic exercise.

02:16:19.560 --> 02:16:20.560
[Guest]: It actually happens, right?

02:16:20.560 --> 02:16:21.560
[Guest]: They do a census assessment

02:16:21.560 --> 02:16:22.560
[Guest]: of every child every year

02:16:22.560 --> 02:16:23.560
[Guest]: to kind of say,

02:16:23.560 --> 02:16:24.560
[Guest]: are children learning?

02:16:24.560 --> 02:16:25.560
[Guest]: And in fact,

02:16:25.560 --> 02:16:26.560
[Guest]: the exercise is so comprehensive

02:16:26.560 --> 02:16:28.560
[Guest]: that NITI Aayog had actually put this

02:16:28.560 --> 02:16:29.560
[Guest]: as one of their examples

02:16:29.560 --> 02:16:30.560
[Guest]: of best practices in the country,

02:16:30.560 --> 02:16:32.560
[Guest]: okay, for education measurement.

02:16:32.560 --> 02:16:34.560
[Guest]: So the elephant in the room,

02:16:34.560 --> 02:16:35.560
[Guest]: and that's this kind of beautiful paper

02:16:35.560 --> 02:16:37.560
[Guest]: by my colleague Abhijit Singh,

02:16:37.560 --> 02:16:38.560
[Guest]: you know, that's just come out

02:16:38.560 --> 02:16:39.560
[Guest]: as a working paper,

02:16:39.560 --> 02:16:40.560
[Guest]: and it's called

02:16:40.560 --> 02:16:41.560
[Guest]: The Myth of Official Measurement, right?

02:16:41.560 --> 02:16:42.560
[Guest]: And so what it does,

02:16:42.560 --> 02:16:43.560
[Guest]: going back to

02:16:43.560 --> 02:16:44.560
[Guest]: asliyat se lagav, right?

02:16:44.560 --> 02:16:47.560
[Guest]: It just takes a random sample of schools

02:16:47.560 --> 02:16:48.560
[Guest]: and a random sample of kids

02:16:48.560 --> 02:16:50.560
[Guest]: and retests the same children

02:16:50.560 --> 02:16:52.560
[Guest]: on a subset of the same questions,

02:16:52.560 --> 02:16:53.560
[Guest]: okay, two months later,

02:16:53.560 --> 02:16:55.560
[Guest]: and finds that the true learning level

02:16:55.560 --> 02:16:57.560
[Guest]: is actually remarkably lower.

02:16:57.560 --> 02:16:58.560
[Guest]: Now, and it's a very interesting

02:16:58.560 --> 02:17:00.560
[Guest]: kind of data fudging, okay,

02:17:00.560 --> 02:17:01.560
[Guest]: which is if you look at

02:17:01.560 --> 02:17:02.560
[Guest]: the ranking of the students,

02:17:02.560 --> 02:17:03.560
[Guest]: the ranking of the students

02:17:03.560 --> 02:17:04.560
[Guest]: is exactly the same, okay?

02:17:04.560 --> 02:17:07.560
[Guest]: So on our independent tests

02:17:07.560 --> 02:17:08.560
[Guest]: as well as the official data,

02:17:08.560 --> 02:17:10.560
[Guest]: the ranking is not fudged, okay?

02:17:10.560 --> 02:17:12.560
[Guest]: But what is fudged is the level.

02:17:12.560 --> 02:17:13.560
[Guest]: So that, and that fudging

02:17:13.560 --> 02:17:15.560
[Guest]: is disproportionate at the bottom

02:17:15.560 --> 02:17:16.560
[Guest]: because there might be children

02:17:16.560 --> 02:17:17.560
[Guest]: who can't do anything

02:17:17.560 --> 02:17:18.560
[Guest]: and they will still be shown

02:17:18.560 --> 02:17:20.560
[Guest]: like as being able to do the question.

02:17:20.560 --> 02:17:22.560
[Guest]: And again, this reflects the fact

02:17:22.560 --> 02:17:24.560
[Guest]: that the system understands

02:17:24.560 --> 02:17:25.560
[Guest]: that at its core,

02:17:25.560 --> 02:17:26.560
[Guest]: it is a sorting system

02:17:26.560 --> 02:17:27.560
[Guest]: and not a human development system.

02:17:27.560 --> 02:17:29.560
[Guest]: So the reason you don't compromise

02:17:29.560 --> 02:17:30.560
[Guest]: with the ranks

02:17:30.560 --> 02:17:31.560
[Guest]: is because the ranks will matter

02:17:31.560 --> 02:17:33.560
[Guest]: for a child at some point in the future

02:17:33.560 --> 02:17:34.560
[Guest]: and it is unfair

02:17:34.560 --> 02:17:36.560
[Guest]: if I flip the rank, okay?

02:17:36.560 --> 02:17:37.560
[Guest]: But you don't mind compromising

02:17:37.560 --> 02:17:39.560
[Guest]: the absolute levels of learning, right?

02:17:39.560 --> 02:17:41.560
[Guest]: Like, you know, because who cares?

02:17:41.560 --> 02:17:42.560
[Guest]: And teachers will then say,

02:17:42.560 --> 02:17:43.560
[Guest]: okay, if I show this child

02:17:43.560 --> 02:17:44.560
[Guest]: is not performing,

02:17:44.560 --> 02:17:46.560
[Guest]: then I will have to do remedial education

02:17:46.560 --> 02:17:47.560
[Guest]: and who will do that, okay?

02:17:47.560 --> 02:17:49.560
[Guest]: So the entire FLN mission will fail

02:17:49.560 --> 02:17:51.560
[Guest]: if you don't have, you know,

02:17:51.560 --> 02:17:52.560
[Guest]: not only administrative data

02:17:52.560 --> 02:17:53.560
[Guest]: at the level of every child,

02:17:53.560 --> 02:17:55.560
[Guest]: but a system of administrative data

02:17:55.560 --> 02:17:57.560
[Guest]: integrity of making sure.

02:17:57.560 --> 02:17:59.560
[Guest]: So, and in some ways, again,

02:17:59.560 --> 02:18:00.560
[Guest]: this is all chapter

02:18:00.560 --> 02:18:01.560
[Guest]: and outcome measurement in my book

02:18:01.560 --> 02:18:02.560
[Guest]: where I talk about, you know,

02:18:02.560 --> 02:18:04.560
[Guest]: a structure of nested supervision

02:18:04.560 --> 02:18:05.560
[Guest]: where you can,

02:18:05.560 --> 02:18:06.560
[Guest]: the kind of inspection we did,

02:18:06.560 --> 02:18:07.560
[Guest]: it's not that difficult

02:18:07.560 --> 02:18:09.560
[Guest]: to actually build into a system.

02:18:09.560 --> 02:18:10.560
[Guest]: And the key is that

02:18:10.560 --> 02:18:11.560
[Guest]: you hold the teacher accountable,

02:18:11.560 --> 02:18:12.560
[Guest]: not just for outcomes,

02:18:12.560 --> 02:18:14.560
[Guest]: but accountable for the truth, okay?

02:18:14.560 --> 02:18:15.560
[Guest]: So coming back to

02:18:15.560 --> 02:18:17.560
[Guest]: system ko asliyat se lagab hone chahiye, right?

02:18:17.560 --> 02:18:18.560
[Guest]: Like I mean,

02:18:18.560 --> 02:18:19.560
[Guest]: which is how you will actually

02:18:19.560 --> 02:18:20.560
[Guest]: deliver outcome, right?

02:18:20.560 --> 02:18:21.560
[Guest]: So this is then

02:18:21.560 --> 02:18:22.560
[Guest]: the nitty-gritty plumbing

02:18:22.560 --> 02:18:23.560
[Guest]: that is not in the policy document,

02:18:23.560 --> 02:18:24.560
[Guest]: but that comes from our research

02:18:24.560 --> 02:18:25.560
[Guest]: and shows how important

02:18:25.560 --> 02:18:27.560
[Guest]: this is going to be, right?

02:18:27.560 --> 02:18:29.560
[Guest]: So you need the goal clarity,

02:18:29.560 --> 02:18:31.560
[Guest]: you need a system of administrative data

02:18:31.560 --> 02:18:32.560
[Guest]: on learning outcomes

02:18:32.560 --> 02:18:33.560
[Guest]: with data integrity

02:18:33.560 --> 02:18:35.560
[Guest]: so that at the level of the child,

02:18:35.560 --> 02:18:36.560
[Guest]: you're able to follow progress

02:18:36.560 --> 02:18:37.560
[Guest]: and make sure that you're getting

02:18:37.560 --> 02:18:38.560
[Guest]: the interventions needed

02:18:38.560 --> 02:18:40.560
[Guest]: to be able to succeed, okay?

02:18:40.560 --> 02:18:42.560
[Guest]: So then the third key part of this

02:18:42.560 --> 02:18:43.560
[Guest]: is the pedagogy itself, right?

02:18:43.560 --> 02:18:45.560
[Guest]: So going back to what I said,

02:18:45.560 --> 02:18:46.560
[Guest]: the tyranny of the syllabus

02:18:46.560 --> 02:18:47.560
[Guest]: and the tyranny of that exam

02:18:47.560 --> 02:18:48.560
[Guest]: is not going to go away

02:18:48.560 --> 02:18:49.560
[Guest]: anytime soon, okay?

02:18:49.560 --> 02:18:51.560
[Guest]: So, and the teacher is still going to face

02:18:51.560 --> 02:18:53.560
[Guest]: this fundamental tension between

02:18:53.560 --> 02:18:54.560
[Guest]: should I complete the portion

02:18:54.560 --> 02:18:55.560
[Guest]: or should I be doing

02:18:55.560 --> 02:18:57.560
[Guest]: customized instruction for children

02:18:57.560 --> 02:18:58.560
[Guest]: who are below the levels?

02:18:58.560 --> 02:19:00.560
[Guest]: And so concretely speaking,

02:19:00.560 --> 02:19:02.560
[Guest]: there are NGOs like Pratham

02:19:02.560 --> 02:19:04.560
[Guest]: and Madhi in Tamil Nadu

02:19:04.560 --> 02:19:07.560
[Guest]: who've done a lot of micro-optimizing

02:19:07.560 --> 02:19:08.560
[Guest]: of the time within the classroom.

02:19:08.560 --> 02:19:10.560
[Guest]: And the best practice right now

02:19:10.560 --> 02:19:13.560
[Guest]: is that you have about 90 minutes a day

02:19:13.560 --> 02:19:14.560
[Guest]: in the timetable,

02:19:14.560 --> 02:19:15.560
[Guest]: which is meant to be for revision

02:19:15.560 --> 02:19:16.560
[Guest]: or supervised work, okay?

02:19:16.560 --> 02:19:18.560
[Guest]: So it's very difficult to tell a teacher

02:19:18.560 --> 02:19:20.560
[Guest]: to take away some of your regular periods

02:19:20.560 --> 02:19:22.560
[Guest]: because the syllabus completion pressure

02:19:22.560 --> 02:19:23.560
[Guest]: is very real.

02:19:23.560 --> 02:19:25.560
[Guest]: But then you can use that other 90 minutes

02:19:25.560 --> 02:19:27.560
[Guest]: of unstructured time to say,

02:19:27.560 --> 02:19:29.560
[Guest]: okay, now let me do the additional work

02:19:29.560 --> 02:19:30.560
[Guest]: on foundational literacy and numeracy

02:19:30.560 --> 02:19:32.560
[Guest]: to make this happen, okay?

02:19:32.560 --> 02:19:34.560
[Guest]: So that is the pedagogy piece of this.

02:19:34.560 --> 02:19:35.560
[Guest]: So you need the goal clarity.

02:19:35.560 --> 02:19:36.560
[Guest]: You need to be able to measure that

02:19:36.560 --> 02:19:37.560
[Guest]: with integrity.

02:19:37.560 --> 02:19:38.560
[Guest]: You need to direct your pedagogy

02:19:38.560 --> 02:19:39.560
[Guest]: towards delivering that.

02:19:39.560 --> 02:19:41.560
[Guest]: And then there's, of course, you know,

02:19:41.560 --> 02:19:43.560
[Guest]: so there's the governance piece overall.

02:19:43.560 --> 02:19:44.560
[Guest]: And frankly, I think, you know,

02:19:44.560 --> 02:19:45.560
[Guest]: even more than attendance,

02:19:45.560 --> 02:19:47.560
[Guest]: which even though my own work

02:19:47.560 --> 02:19:48.560
[Guest]: has been on attendance,

02:19:48.560 --> 02:19:49.560
[Guest]: I think, you know, it can get a little,

02:19:49.560 --> 02:19:50.560
[Guest]: you know, really intrusive

02:19:50.560 --> 02:19:52.560
[Guest]: to then say I'm going to do cameras

02:19:52.560 --> 02:19:53.560
[Guest]: and biometric scanners

02:19:53.560 --> 02:19:54.560
[Guest]: because frankly, in the end,

02:19:54.560 --> 02:19:56.560
[Guest]: I don't want to kind of invade

02:19:56.560 --> 02:19:57.560
[Guest]: the teacher's sense of agency

02:19:57.560 --> 02:19:58.560
[Guest]: as long as the outcomes are done, right?

02:19:58.560 --> 02:20:00.560
[Guest]: So I would much rather have a culture

02:20:00.560 --> 02:20:02.560
[Guest]: of autonomy on process

02:20:02.560 --> 02:20:03.560
[Guest]: and accountability of outcomes.

02:20:03.560 --> 02:20:05.560
[Guest]: And if the governance machinery

02:20:05.560 --> 02:20:07.560
[Guest]: is able to ensure administrative data

02:20:07.560 --> 02:20:09.560
[Guest]: integrity and learning outcomes

02:20:09.560 --> 02:20:10.560
[Guest]: for every child,

02:20:10.560 --> 02:20:12.560
[Guest]: I am reasonably confident

02:20:12.560 --> 02:20:13.560
[Guest]: that the system is capable

02:20:13.560 --> 02:20:14.560
[Guest]: of delivering improved outcomes.

02:20:14.560 --> 02:20:15.560
[Guest]: Once you know that,

02:20:15.560 --> 02:20:17.560
[Guest]: this cannot be fudged, okay?

02:20:17.560 --> 02:20:18.560
[Guest]: And then there is a piece

02:20:18.560 --> 02:20:19.560
[Guest]: of actually providing

02:20:19.560 --> 02:20:21.560
[Guest]: supplemental instructional resources.

02:20:21.560 --> 02:20:23.560
[Guest]: And so, you know, ideally,

02:20:23.560 --> 02:20:24.560
[Guest]: there would be a way

02:20:24.560 --> 02:20:26.560
[Guest]: to hire kind of teaching assistants

02:20:26.560 --> 02:20:28.560
[Guest]: or, you know, contract teachers or,

02:20:28.560 --> 02:20:29.560
[Guest]: you know, on short-term,

02:20:29.560 --> 02:20:31.560
[Guest]: two-hour, three-hour as a day

02:20:31.560 --> 02:20:33.560
[Guest]: to provide that additional instruction

02:20:33.560 --> 02:20:34.560
[Guest]: to the children who are falling behind.

02:20:34.560 --> 02:20:36.560
[Guest]: And that can be incredibly cost-effective

02:20:36.560 --> 02:20:37.560
[Guest]: as we've seen in study after study.

02:20:37.560 --> 02:20:38.560
[Guest]: So, and I'll come back

02:20:38.560 --> 02:20:40.560
[Guest]: to my third big idea

02:20:40.560 --> 02:20:41.560
[Guest]: where I will integrate this, okay?

02:20:41.560 --> 02:20:43.560
[Guest]: So I think the first part of this

02:20:43.560 --> 02:20:44.560
[Guest]: is the FLM mission that's there,

02:20:44.560 --> 02:20:46.560
[Guest]: and I think the MHRD is going to come up

02:20:46.560 --> 02:20:47.560
[Guest]: with these frameworks.

02:20:47.560 --> 02:20:48.560
[Guest]: So, but the key thing

02:20:48.560 --> 02:20:49.560
[Guest]: is going to be getting

02:20:49.560 --> 02:20:50.560
[Guest]: to this next level of detail

02:20:50.560 --> 02:20:51.560
[Guest]: of measurement

02:20:51.560 --> 02:20:52.560
[Guest]: as well as data integrity,

02:20:52.560 --> 02:20:53.560
[Guest]: which is not in the NAP,

02:20:53.560 --> 02:20:55.560
[Guest]: but which will need to happen, okay?

02:20:55.560 --> 02:20:57.560
[Guest]: So that's, I think, point number one.

02:20:57.560 --> 02:20:58.560
[Guest]: Does that make sense?

02:20:58.560 --> 02:20:59.560
[Amit Varma]: Any response, reaction?

02:20:59.560 --> 02:21:00.560
[Amit Varma]: It makes sense.

02:21:00.560 --> 02:21:01.560
[Amit Varma]: I mean, my response that is like,

02:21:01.560 --> 02:21:02.560
[Amit Varma]: first of all,

02:21:02.560 --> 02:21:03.560
[Amit Varma]: when you started speaking of goals,

02:21:03.560 --> 02:21:04.560
[Amit Varma]: I immediately thought that,

02:21:04.560 --> 02:21:05.560
[Amit Varma]: wait a minute,

02:21:05.560 --> 02:21:06.560
[Amit Varma]: like, you know,

02:21:06.560 --> 02:21:07.560
[Amit Varma]: like when I speak to,

02:21:07.560 --> 02:21:08.560
[Amit Varma]: I teach a class on writing.

02:21:08.560 --> 02:21:09.560
[Amit Varma]: So when I,

02:21:09.560 --> 02:21:10.560
[Amit Varma]: I always tell my writing students

02:21:10.560 --> 02:21:11.560
[Amit Varma]: that, you know,

02:21:11.560 --> 02:21:12.560
[Amit Varma]: everybody has goals.

02:21:12.560 --> 02:21:13.560
[Amit Varma]: Bad writers will have the same goals

02:21:13.560 --> 02:21:14.560
[Amit Varma]: as the good writers.

02:21:14.560 --> 02:21:15.560
[Amit Varma]: What is important is the process.

02:21:15.560 --> 02:21:17.560
[Amit Varma]: But then I get what you're saying,

02:21:17.560 --> 02:21:18.560
[Amit Varma]: that we should at least begin

02:21:18.560 --> 02:21:19.560
[Amit Varma]: by having clarity

02:21:19.560 --> 02:21:21.560
[Unknown]: of what are we trying to achieve.

02:21:21.560 --> 02:21:22.560
[Unknown]: And if these are the outcomes

02:21:22.560 --> 02:21:23.560
[Amit Varma]: we're trying to achieve

02:21:23.560 --> 02:21:24.560
[Amit Varma]: and we have that clarity,

02:21:24.560 --> 02:21:26.560
[Amit Varma]: then those goals are very useful

02:21:26.560 --> 02:21:27.560
[Amit Varma]: if they are then communicated

02:21:27.560 --> 02:21:28.560
[Amit Varma]: to everyone.

02:21:28.560 --> 02:21:31.560
[Amit Varma]: Where I feel a little skeptical

02:21:31.560 --> 02:21:33.560
[Amit Varma]: of what happens after that

02:21:33.560 --> 02:21:34.560
[Amit Varma]: is when you talk about

02:21:34.560 --> 02:21:36.560
[Amit Varma]: the integrity of measuring it,

02:21:36.560 --> 02:21:37.560
[Amit Varma]: because my experience in India,

02:21:37.560 --> 02:21:38.560
[Amit Varma]: which is, you know,

02:21:38.560 --> 02:21:41.560
[Amit Varma]: the center of Jugaad in the whole world,

02:21:41.560 --> 02:21:42.560
[Amit Varma]: is that if there is a metric,

02:21:42.560 --> 02:21:43.560
[Amit Varma]: it will be gamed.

02:21:43.560 --> 02:21:44.560
[Guest]: Correct.

02:21:44.560 --> 02:21:45.560
[Guest]: And I agree, right?

02:21:45.560 --> 02:21:46.560
[Guest]: So, and I think, see,

02:21:46.560 --> 02:21:47.560
[Guest]: in the end,

02:21:47.560 --> 02:21:48.560
[Guest]: these are all about probabilities, right?

02:21:48.560 --> 02:21:49.560
[Guest]: So you'll have about 20%

02:21:49.560 --> 02:21:50.560
[Guest]: of teachers and administrators

02:21:50.560 --> 02:21:51.560
[Guest]: who will be high integrity.

02:21:51.560 --> 02:21:52.560
[Guest]: There'll be 20%

02:21:52.560 --> 02:21:53.560
[Guest]: who you will never be able

02:21:53.560 --> 02:21:54.560
[Guest]: to fix.

02:21:54.560 --> 02:21:55.560
[Guest]: But that middle 60%

02:21:55.560 --> 02:21:56.560
[Guest]: does respond, right?

02:21:56.560 --> 02:21:57.560
[Guest]: Like, you know,

02:21:57.560 --> 02:21:58.560
[Guest]: to what the overall thrust

02:21:58.560 --> 02:21:59.560
[Guest]: from the system is.

02:21:59.560 --> 02:22:01.560
[Guest]: And I think, you know,

02:22:01.560 --> 02:22:03.560
[Guest]: we have additional micro evidence

02:22:03.560 --> 02:22:04.560
[Guest]: on how using technology

02:22:04.560 --> 02:22:06.560
[Guest]: for measurement can, you know,

02:22:06.560 --> 02:22:07.560
[Guest]: really be a game changer

02:22:07.560 --> 02:22:08.560
[Guest]: for data integrity

02:22:08.560 --> 02:22:09.560
[Guest]: because then it's kind of

02:22:09.560 --> 02:22:10.560
[Guest]: real-time measurement

02:22:10.560 --> 02:22:11.560
[Guest]: that gets uploaded.

02:22:11.560 --> 02:22:12.560
[Guest]: It's hard to fudge.

02:22:12.560 --> 02:22:13.560
[Guest]: It's hard to, you know.

02:22:13.560 --> 02:22:14.560
[Guest]: So we've done a bunch

02:22:14.560 --> 02:22:15.560
[Guest]: of pilots on this.

02:22:15.560 --> 02:22:16.560
[Guest]: And I think a bunch

02:22:16.560 --> 02:22:17.560
[Guest]: of these inputs,

02:22:17.560 --> 02:22:18.560
[Guest]: we will probably put in a memo

02:22:18.560 --> 02:22:19.560
[Guest]: and send to MHRD

02:22:19.560 --> 02:22:20.560
[Guest]: and, you know, send to states.

02:22:20.560 --> 02:22:21.560
[Guest]: And hopefully some of that

02:22:21.560 --> 02:22:22.560
[Guest]: gets reflected

02:22:22.560 --> 02:22:23.560
[Guest]: because the NEP

02:22:23.560 --> 02:22:24.560
[Guest]: has been announced,

02:22:24.560 --> 02:22:25.560
[Guest]: but there is still

02:22:25.560 --> 02:22:26.560
[Guest]: a set of details

02:22:26.560 --> 02:22:27.560
[Guest]: that, you know,

02:22:27.560 --> 02:22:28.560
[Amit Varma]: still has to show up.

02:22:28.560 --> 02:22:29.560
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, that makes sense.

02:22:29.560 --> 02:22:30.560
[Guest]: I mean, so let's move on from there.

02:22:30.560 --> 02:22:31.560
[Guest]: Yeah.

02:22:31.560 --> 02:22:32.560
[Guest]: So then coming back

02:22:32.560 --> 02:22:33.560
[Guest]: to cost effectiveness.

02:22:33.560 --> 02:22:34.560
[Guest]: So I think,

02:22:34.560 --> 02:22:35.560
[Guest]: so one thing which NEP

02:22:35.560 --> 02:22:36.560
[Guest]: does talk about,

02:22:36.560 --> 02:22:37.560
[Guest]: it talks a little bit

02:22:37.560 --> 02:22:38.560
[Guest]: about school consolidation.

02:22:38.560 --> 02:22:39.560
[Guest]: Sorry, school complexes,

02:22:39.560 --> 02:22:40.560
[Guest]: not school consolidation.

02:22:40.560 --> 02:22:41.560
[Guest]: But let me again

02:22:41.560 --> 02:22:42.560
[Guest]: provide some facts

02:22:42.560 --> 02:22:43.560
[Guest]: for your listeners, right?

02:22:43.560 --> 02:22:44.560
[Guest]: So one of the problems

02:22:44.560 --> 02:22:45.560
[Guest]: of our approach to access

02:22:45.560 --> 02:22:46.560
[Guest]: of creating schools

02:22:46.560 --> 02:22:47.560
[Guest]: within a kilometer

02:22:47.560 --> 02:22:48.560
[Guest]: of every habitation

02:22:48.560 --> 02:22:49.560
[Guest]: is that 20 years ago,

02:22:49.560 --> 02:22:51.560
[Guest]: that may have been necessary

02:22:51.560 --> 02:22:52.560
[Guest]: to get marginalized groups

02:22:52.560 --> 02:22:53.560
[Guest]: into school

02:22:53.560 --> 02:22:54.560
[Guest]: because they would not

02:22:54.560 --> 02:22:55.560
[Guest]: be able to travel, right?

02:22:55.560 --> 02:22:56.560
[Guest]: But one of the consequences

02:22:56.560 --> 02:22:57.560
[Guest]: of this is that

02:22:57.560 --> 02:22:58.560
[Guest]: your public schooling system,

02:22:58.560 --> 02:22:59.560
[Guest]: the countryside,

02:22:59.560 --> 02:23:00.560
[Guest]: is pockmarked

02:23:00.560 --> 02:23:01.560
[Guest]: with these subscale schools

02:23:01.560 --> 02:23:02.560
[Guest]: with enrollment

02:23:02.560 --> 02:23:03.560
[Guest]: of about 20, 30 children.

02:23:03.560 --> 02:23:04.560
[Guest]: Then you have five grades,

02:23:04.560 --> 02:23:05.560
[Guest]: two teachers,

02:23:05.560 --> 02:23:06.560
[Guest]: and, you know,

02:23:06.560 --> 02:23:07.560
[Guest]: it's bad for governance,

02:23:07.560 --> 02:23:08.560
[Guest]: it's bad for pedagogy,

02:23:08.560 --> 02:23:09.560
[Guest]: and it's bad for cost effectiveness,

02:23:09.560 --> 02:23:10.560
[Guest]: right?

02:23:10.560 --> 02:23:11.560
[Guest]: So it's bad for governance

02:23:11.560 --> 02:23:12.560
[Guest]: because going back

02:23:12.560 --> 02:23:13.560
[Guest]: to my point

02:23:13.560 --> 02:23:14.560
[Guest]: about monitoring visits,

02:23:14.560 --> 02:23:15.560
[Guest]: it's really hard

02:23:15.560 --> 02:23:16.560
[Guest]: to go and visit like,

02:23:16.560 --> 02:23:17.560
[Guest]: you know, every school

02:23:17.560 --> 02:23:18.560
[Guest]: that is so far out

02:23:18.560 --> 02:23:19.560
[Guest]: and remote

02:23:19.560 --> 02:23:20.560
[Guest]: and you have limited

02:23:20.560 --> 02:23:21.560
[Guest]: capacity.

02:23:21.560 --> 02:23:22.560
[Guest]: It's bad for pedagogy

02:23:22.560 --> 02:23:23.560
[Guest]: because you,

02:23:23.560 --> 02:23:24.560
[Guest]: by construction,

02:23:24.560 --> 02:23:25.560
[Guest]: you have multi-grade teaching.

02:23:25.560 --> 02:23:26.560
[Guest]: The two teachers

02:23:26.560 --> 02:23:27.560
[Guest]: are now teaching simultaneously

02:23:27.560 --> 02:23:28.560
[Guest]: across five grades,

02:23:28.560 --> 02:23:29.560
[Guest]: so it gets really,

02:23:29.560 --> 02:23:30.560
[Guest]: really hard

02:23:30.560 --> 02:23:31.560
[Guest]: even for a motivated teacher

02:23:31.560 --> 02:23:32.560
[Guest]: to deal with that.

02:23:32.560 --> 02:23:33.560
[Guest]: And it is also really bad

02:23:33.560 --> 02:23:34.560
[Guest]: for value for money

02:23:34.560 --> 02:23:35.560
[Guest]: and that's because

02:23:35.560 --> 02:23:36.560
[Guest]: you have a norm

02:23:36.560 --> 02:23:37.560
[Guest]: of minimum two teachers.

02:23:37.560 --> 02:23:38.560
[Guest]: You end up with PTRs

02:23:38.560 --> 02:23:39.560
[Guest]: of about 10 to 15

02:23:39.560 --> 02:23:40.560
[Guest]: in these places,

02:23:40.560 --> 02:23:41.560
[Guest]: which is pupil-teacher ratio,

02:23:41.560 --> 02:23:42.560
[Guest]: so the cost per child

02:23:42.560 --> 02:23:43.560
[Guest]: in these small schools

02:23:43.560 --> 02:23:44.560
[Guest]: ends up being,

02:23:44.560 --> 02:23:45.560
[Guest]: you know,

02:23:45.560 --> 02:23:46.560
[Guest]: from the few states

02:23:46.560 --> 02:23:47.560
[Guest]: where I've calculated the data,

02:23:47.560 --> 02:23:48.560
[Guest]: ends up being over 75,

02:23:48.560 --> 02:23:49.560
[Guest]: sometimes 80,000

02:23:49.560 --> 02:23:50.560
[Guest]: sometimes 80,000 rupees

02:23:50.560 --> 02:23:51.560
[Guest]: a year per child

02:23:51.560 --> 02:23:52.560
[Guest]: compared to an average

02:23:52.560 --> 02:23:53.560
[Guest]: cost per child

02:23:53.560 --> 02:23:54.560
[Guest]: of maybe 30,000-35,000

02:23:54.560 --> 02:23:55.560
[Guest]: if you are at a scale

02:23:55.560 --> 02:23:56.560
[Guest]: of about 30.

02:23:56.560 --> 02:23:57.560
[Guest]: Okay?

02:23:57.560 --> 02:23:58.560
[Guest]: So one simple idea

02:23:58.560 --> 02:23:59.560
[Guest]: is that

02:23:59.560 --> 02:24:00.560
[Guest]: there is a trade-off

02:24:00.560 --> 02:24:01.560
[Guest]: obviously between

02:24:01.560 --> 02:24:02.560
[Guest]: access and scale, right?

02:24:02.560 --> 02:24:03.560
[Guest]: So if I try to provide access

02:24:03.560 --> 02:24:04.560
[Guest]: in this way

02:24:04.560 --> 02:24:05.560
[Guest]: of building schools,

02:24:05.560 --> 02:24:06.560
[Guest]: you're losing scale, right?

02:24:06.560 --> 02:24:07.560
[Guest]: Now, an alternative way

02:24:07.560 --> 02:24:08.560
[Guest]: of providing access,

02:24:08.560 --> 02:24:09.560
[Guest]: which is what we see

02:24:09.560 --> 02:24:10.560
[Guest]: in our Bihar girls

02:24:10.560 --> 02:24:11.560
[Guest]: bicycle paper

02:24:11.560 --> 02:24:12.560
[Guest]: where we see that

02:24:12.560 --> 02:24:13.560
[Guest]: that was an incredibly

02:24:13.560 --> 02:24:14.560
[Guest]: effective program, right,

02:24:14.560 --> 02:24:15.560
[Guest]: is that you can have

02:24:15.560 --> 02:24:16.560
[Guest]: schools at larger scale

02:24:16.560 --> 02:24:17.560
[Guest]: in the middle

02:24:17.560 --> 02:24:18.560
[Guest]: of a gram panchayat

02:24:18.560 --> 02:24:19.560
[Guest]: and be able

02:24:19.560 --> 02:24:20.560
[Guest]: to provide transport, right?

02:24:20.560 --> 02:24:21.560
[Guest]: Like, you need to have

02:24:21.560 --> 02:24:22.560
[Guest]: a larger catchment area

02:24:22.560 --> 02:24:23.560
[Guest]: and you don't even have

02:24:23.560 --> 02:24:24.560
[Guest]: to provide

02:24:24.560 --> 02:24:25.560
[Guest]: transport vouchers.

02:24:25.560 --> 02:24:26.560
[Guest]: You can literally

02:24:26.560 --> 02:24:27.560
[Guest]: run a bus service, right?

02:24:27.560 --> 02:24:28.560
[Guest]: You can run a bus

02:24:28.560 --> 02:24:29.560
[Guest]: or you can contract

02:24:29.560 --> 02:24:30.560
[Guest]: a bus service to say,

02:24:30.560 --> 02:24:31.560
[Guest]: here is my catchment area

02:24:31.560 --> 02:24:32.560
[Guest]: that's actually

02:24:32.560 --> 02:24:33.560
[Guest]: two or three kilometers

02:24:33.560 --> 02:24:34.560
[Guest]: and I'm just going to

02:24:34.560 --> 02:24:35.560
[Guest]: go pick up children

02:24:35.560 --> 02:24:36.560
[Guest]: and then have this

02:24:36.560 --> 02:24:37.560
[Guest]: focal school

02:24:37.560 --> 02:24:38.560
[Guest]: in the middle of the gram panchayat

02:24:38.560 --> 02:24:39.560
[Guest]: or anywhere else

02:24:39.560 --> 02:24:40.560
[Guest]: in kind of, you know,

02:24:40.560 --> 02:24:41.560
[Guest]: what your catchment area is

02:24:41.560 --> 02:24:42.560
[Guest]: and then once you have

02:24:42.560 --> 02:24:43.560
[Guest]: enrollment of about

02:24:43.560 --> 02:24:44.560
[Guest]: 150 to 200, right,

02:24:44.560 --> 02:24:45.560
[Guest]: then you're at a place

02:24:45.560 --> 02:24:46.560
[Guest]: where you have

02:24:46.560 --> 02:24:47.560
[Guest]: much better pedagogy

02:24:47.560 --> 02:24:48.560
[Guest]: of teacher per subject.

02:24:48.560 --> 02:24:49.560
[Guest]: You have much better

02:24:49.560 --> 02:24:50.560
[Guest]: governance because

02:24:50.560 --> 02:24:51.560
[Guest]: you can have a principal.

02:24:51.560 --> 02:24:52.560
[Guest]: You actually get

02:24:52.560 --> 02:24:53.560
[Guest]: better teacher morale

02:24:53.560 --> 02:24:54.560
[Guest]: because teachers actually

02:24:54.560 --> 02:24:55.560
[Guest]: enjoy having a community

02:24:55.560 --> 02:24:56.560
[Guest]: of peers as opposed

02:24:56.560 --> 02:24:57.560
[Guest]: to being out there

02:24:57.560 --> 02:24:58.560
[Guest]: in the village

02:24:58.560 --> 02:24:59.560
[Guest]: as the only kind

02:24:59.560 --> 02:25:00.560
[Guest]: of educated person

02:25:00.560 --> 02:25:01.560
[Guest]: and you also get

02:25:01.560 --> 02:25:02.560
[Guest]: much better value for money

02:25:02.560 --> 02:25:03.560
[Guest]: and that gives you

02:25:03.560 --> 02:25:04.560
[Guest]: the scale that allows you

02:25:04.560 --> 02:25:05.560
[Guest]: to then invest in

02:25:05.560 --> 02:25:06.560
[Guest]: whether it's the computers

02:25:06.560 --> 02:25:07.560
[Guest]: or the, you know,

02:25:07.560 --> 02:25:08.560
[Guest]: or the other facilities.

02:25:08.560 --> 02:25:09.560
[Guest]: So, you know,

02:25:09.560 --> 02:25:10.560
[Guest]: I think 20 years ago,

02:25:10.560 --> 02:25:11.560
[Guest]: 25 years ago,

02:25:11.560 --> 02:25:12.560
[Guest]: it might seem that

02:25:12.560 --> 02:25:13.560
[Guest]: this was unrealistic

02:25:13.560 --> 02:25:14.560
[Guest]: because we didn't have

02:25:14.560 --> 02:25:15.560
[Guest]: the road transport infrastructure

02:25:15.560 --> 02:25:16.560
[Guest]: but given the investments

02:25:16.560 --> 02:25:17.560
[Guest]: in roads and all of that,

02:25:17.560 --> 02:25:18.560
[Guest]: in fact, there's a very

02:25:18.560 --> 02:25:19.560
[Guest]: nice study by

02:25:19.560 --> 02:25:21.560
[Guest]: Shilpa Aggarwal at ISB

02:25:21.560 --> 02:25:22.560
[Guest]: looking at, I think,

02:25:22.560 --> 02:25:23.560
[Guest]: you know, child mortality,

02:25:23.560 --> 02:25:24.560
[Guest]: maternal mortality,

02:25:24.560 --> 02:25:25.560
[Guest]: I'm not sure

02:25:25.560 --> 02:25:26.560
[Guest]: on what the exact outcome is

02:25:26.560 --> 02:25:27.560
[Guest]: but what it shows is that

02:25:27.560 --> 02:25:28.560
[Guest]: in fact that you get

02:25:28.560 --> 02:25:29.560
[Guest]: much better health outcomes

02:25:29.560 --> 02:25:30.560
[Guest]: from investing in roads

02:25:30.560 --> 02:25:32.560
[Guest]: than from investing in clinics

02:25:32.560 --> 02:25:33.560
[Guest]: and that's because

02:25:33.560 --> 02:25:34.560
[Guest]: the clinics,

02:25:34.560 --> 02:25:35.560
[Guest]: when you build them remotely,

02:25:35.560 --> 02:25:36.560
[Guest]: these are sub-scale

02:25:36.560 --> 02:25:37.560
[Guest]: and they're not used as often

02:25:37.560 --> 02:25:38.560
[Guest]: whereas when you build the roads,

02:25:38.560 --> 02:25:39.560
[Guest]: you're able to bring people

02:25:39.560 --> 02:25:41.560
[Guest]: to where the scale facility is, right?

02:25:41.560 --> 02:25:42.560
[Guest]: So that same logic,

02:25:42.560 --> 02:25:43.560
[Guest]: I think, can apply

02:25:43.560 --> 02:25:44.560
[Guest]: with the logistics

02:25:44.560 --> 02:25:45.560
[Guest]: of how we organize

02:25:45.560 --> 02:25:46.560
[Guest]: our schooling system.

02:25:46.560 --> 02:25:47.560
[Guest]: So this is, again,

02:25:47.560 --> 02:25:49.560
[Guest]: a very plumbing kind of discussion

02:25:49.560 --> 02:25:50.560
[Guest]: but it is enormous

02:25:50.560 --> 02:25:51.560
[Guest]: in terms of cost effectiveness

02:25:51.560 --> 02:25:52.560
[Guest]: because the bulk of our money

02:25:52.560 --> 02:25:53.560
[Guest]: goes to teacher salaries

02:25:53.560 --> 02:25:54.560
[Guest]: and the cost per child

02:25:54.560 --> 02:25:55.560
[Guest]: in these schools

02:25:55.560 --> 02:25:56.560
[Guest]: is about 70, 80, 90,000.

02:25:56.560 --> 02:25:57.560
[Guest]: Okay?

02:25:57.560 --> 02:25:58.560
[Guest]: Now, but coming back

02:25:58.560 --> 02:25:59.560
[Guest]: to political economy,

02:25:59.560 --> 02:26:01.560
[Guest]: what are two of the important

02:26:01.560 --> 02:26:02.560
[Guest]: potential political economy concerns?

02:26:02.560 --> 02:26:04.560
[Guest]: Okay, so the one is that

02:26:04.560 --> 02:26:05.560
[Guest]: local communities

02:26:05.560 --> 02:26:06.560
[Guest]: tend to take a lot of pride

02:26:06.560 --> 02:26:07.560
[Guest]: in their school

02:26:07.560 --> 02:26:08.560
[Guest]: which is often something

02:26:08.560 --> 02:26:09.560
[Guest]: that has been created

02:26:09.560 --> 02:26:10.560
[Guest]: after lobbying a lot

02:26:10.560 --> 02:26:11.560
[Guest]: and then, you know,

02:26:11.560 --> 02:26:12.560
[Guest]: whatever it is,

02:26:12.560 --> 02:26:13.560
[Guest]: like, I mean,

02:26:13.560 --> 02:26:15.560
[Guest]: school is a source of pride

02:26:15.560 --> 02:26:16.560
[Guest]: for a local community.

02:26:16.560 --> 02:26:18.560
[Guest]: So a top-down decision of saying,

02:26:18.560 --> 02:26:19.560
[Guest]: okay, we're going to shut down

02:26:19.560 --> 02:26:20.560
[Guest]: these schools and consolidate

02:26:20.560 --> 02:26:22.560
[Guest]: will backfire on day one, right?

02:26:22.560 --> 02:26:23.560
[Guest]: So what you need

02:26:23.560 --> 02:26:25.560
[Guest]: is to kind of have

02:26:25.560 --> 02:26:26.560
[Guest]: a democratic validation

02:26:26.560 --> 02:26:27.560
[Guest]: of this process

02:26:27.560 --> 02:26:29.560
[Guest]: by having a policy

02:26:29.560 --> 02:26:30.560
[Guest]: or a, you know, project

02:26:30.560 --> 02:26:31.560
[Guest]: that says,

02:26:31.560 --> 02:26:32.560
[Guest]: here is a proposal

02:26:32.560 --> 02:26:33.560
[Guest]: that in this panchayat,

02:26:33.560 --> 02:26:34.560
[Guest]: what this would mean

02:26:34.560 --> 02:26:35.560
[Guest]: is that we would build a school,

02:26:35.560 --> 02:26:36.560
[Guest]: we would provide this transport,

02:26:36.560 --> 02:26:37.560
[Guest]: this is what would happen

02:26:37.560 --> 02:26:38.560
[Guest]: and then let the panchayat

02:26:38.560 --> 02:26:39.560
[Guest]: themselves vote on that, right?

02:26:39.560 --> 02:26:40.560
[Guest]: And say that,

02:26:40.560 --> 02:26:41.560
[Guest]: is this something

02:26:41.560 --> 02:26:42.560
[Guest]: they would like to do?

02:26:42.560 --> 02:26:43.560
[Guest]: And so again,

02:26:43.560 --> 02:26:44.560
[Guest]: as a way of accommodating heterogeneity

02:26:44.560 --> 02:26:45.560
[Guest]: as opposed to going top-down,

02:26:45.560 --> 02:26:47.560
[Guest]: if you have an approach like that,

02:26:47.560 --> 02:26:48.560
[Guest]: maybe there'll be 100 villages,

02:26:48.560 --> 02:26:49.560
[Guest]: 200 villages that say,

02:26:49.560 --> 02:26:50.560
[Guest]: please try this

02:26:50.560 --> 02:26:51.560
[Guest]: and then you try it out

02:26:51.560 --> 02:26:52.560
[Guest]: and then if it works, right,

02:26:52.560 --> 02:26:53.560
[Guest]: then it spreads

02:26:53.560 --> 02:26:54.560
[Guest]: by demonstrated success

02:26:54.560 --> 02:26:55.560
[Guest]: as opposed to trying

02:26:55.560 --> 02:26:56.560
[Guest]: to do this by top-down.

02:26:56.560 --> 02:26:57.560
[Guest]: Sometimes policymakers

02:26:57.560 --> 02:26:58.560
[Guest]: have a view that says,

02:26:58.560 --> 02:26:59.560
[Guest]: no, in India,

02:26:59.560 --> 02:27:00.560
[Guest]: the only way to do things at scale

02:27:00.560 --> 02:27:01.560
[Guest]: is to force it down the throat.

02:27:01.560 --> 02:27:02.560
[Guest]: But, you know,

02:27:02.560 --> 02:27:04.560
[Guest]: going back to the coercive state

02:27:04.560 --> 02:27:05.560
[Guest]: and how do you make democracy

02:27:05.560 --> 02:27:06.560
[Guest]: work better?

02:27:06.560 --> 02:27:07.560
[Guest]: I think, you know,

02:27:07.560 --> 02:27:08.560
[Guest]: where you balance

02:27:08.560 --> 02:27:09.560
[Guest]: the economies of scale

02:27:09.560 --> 02:27:10.560
[Guest]: that come from the higher level

02:27:10.560 --> 02:27:11.560
[Guest]: with kind of the agency

02:27:11.560 --> 02:27:12.560
[Guest]: that you want to provide

02:27:12.560 --> 02:27:13.560
[Guest]: to citizens and communities

02:27:13.560 --> 02:27:16.560
[Guest]: is to use the analytical horsepower

02:27:16.560 --> 02:27:17.560
[Guest]: at a higher level

02:27:17.560 --> 02:27:18.560
[Guest]: to say,

02:27:18.560 --> 02:27:19.560
[Guest]: here are some policy reforms

02:27:19.560 --> 02:27:20.560
[Guest]: that may make sense

02:27:20.560 --> 02:27:21.560
[Guest]: that within a given budget envelope

02:27:21.560 --> 02:27:23.560
[Guest]: can deliver much better outcomes

02:27:23.560 --> 02:27:24.560
[Guest]: and now you,

02:27:24.560 --> 02:27:25.560
[Guest]: the community,

02:27:25.560 --> 02:27:26.560
[Guest]: come back and tell us

02:27:26.560 --> 02:27:27.560
[Guest]: if you would like to do this

02:27:27.560 --> 02:27:28.560
[Guest]: and if you would,

02:27:28.560 --> 02:27:29.560
[Guest]: then, you know,

02:27:29.560 --> 02:27:30.560
[Guest]: let's roll it out, right?

02:27:30.560 --> 02:27:31.560
[Guest]: So I think that would be my approach

02:27:31.560 --> 02:27:32.560
[Guest]: to this larger issue

02:27:32.560 --> 02:27:33.560
[Guest]: of school size optimization,

02:27:33.560 --> 02:27:34.560
[Guest]: I think is the right way to frame it.

02:27:34.560 --> 02:27:35.560
[Guest]: And then from a teacher's perspective,

02:27:35.560 --> 02:27:36.560
[Guest]: there is likely to be

02:27:36.560 --> 02:27:37.560
[Guest]: some union opposition

02:27:37.560 --> 02:27:38.560
[Guest]: because in the long term,

02:27:38.560 --> 02:27:39.560
[Guest]: the cost effectiveness of this

02:27:39.560 --> 02:27:40.560
[Guest]: comes from the fact

02:27:40.560 --> 02:27:41.560
[Guest]: that you're reducing,

02:27:41.560 --> 02:27:42.560
[Guest]: potentially,

02:27:42.560 --> 02:27:43.560
[Guest]: the number of teacher posts, right?

02:27:43.560 --> 02:27:44.560
[Guest]: Because, you know,

02:27:44.560 --> 02:27:45.560
[Guest]: but there are two,

02:27:45.560 --> 02:27:46.560
[Guest]: I think, broad answers to that.

02:27:46.560 --> 02:27:48.560
[Guest]: So one is that, in fact,

02:27:48.560 --> 02:27:49.560
[Guest]: it actually improves

02:27:49.560 --> 02:27:50.560
[Guest]: working conditions

02:27:50.560 --> 02:27:51.560
[Guest]: for teachers significantly, right?

02:27:51.560 --> 02:27:52.560
[Guest]: Because most teachers

02:27:52.560 --> 02:27:53.560
[Guest]: live in urban areas

02:27:53.560 --> 02:27:54.560
[Guest]: and commute to the rural areas.

02:27:54.560 --> 02:27:56.560
[Guest]: So by kind of making the school

02:27:56.560 --> 02:27:57.560
[Guest]: in a more central area,

02:27:57.560 --> 02:27:58.560
[Guest]: you're actually making

02:27:58.560 --> 02:27:59.560
[Guest]: the school more accessible,

02:27:59.560 --> 02:28:01.560
[Guest]: but you're also improving

02:28:01.560 --> 02:28:02.560
[Guest]: the working environment

02:28:02.560 --> 02:28:03.560
[Guest]: by having a profession,

02:28:03.560 --> 02:28:04.560
[Guest]: a community of peers, right?

02:28:04.560 --> 02:28:05.560
[Guest]: You go in,

02:28:05.560 --> 02:28:06.560
[Guest]: it's much more fun to,

02:28:06.560 --> 02:28:07.560
[Guest]: in fact, what we document

02:28:07.560 --> 02:28:08.560
[Guest]: is the absenteeism

02:28:08.560 --> 02:28:09.560
[Guest]: even in healthcare

02:28:09.560 --> 02:28:10.560
[Guest]: that is much lower

02:28:10.560 --> 02:28:11.560
[Guest]: in district hospitals

02:28:11.560 --> 02:28:12.560
[Guest]: than it is kind of

02:28:12.560 --> 02:28:13.560
[Guest]: in the outposts, right?

02:28:13.560 --> 02:28:14.560
[Guest]: Because there is a set of peers,

02:28:14.560 --> 02:28:15.560
[Guest]: there's both peer monitoring

02:28:15.560 --> 02:28:16.560
[Guest]: and there's kind of

02:28:16.560 --> 02:28:17.560
[Guest]: a community of practice, right?

02:28:17.560 --> 02:28:18.560
[Guest]: So I think from a teacher

02:28:18.560 --> 02:28:19.560
[Guest]: working condition perspective,

02:28:19.560 --> 02:28:20.560
[Guest]: this would almost

02:28:20.560 --> 02:28:21.560
[Guest]: certainly be a positive.

02:28:21.560 --> 02:28:23.560
[Guest]: And you're also not firing anybody,

02:28:23.560 --> 02:28:24.560
[Guest]: so you're basically

02:28:24.560 --> 02:28:25.560
[Guest]: ring-fencing this

02:28:25.560 --> 02:28:26.560
[Guest]: and protecting incumbents.

02:28:26.560 --> 02:28:27.560
[Guest]: And so the fiscal savings

02:28:27.560 --> 02:28:28.560
[Guest]: will come over time,

02:28:28.560 --> 02:28:29.560
[Guest]: but this is then something

02:28:29.560 --> 02:28:31.560
[Guest]: that will substantially improve

02:28:31.560 --> 02:28:32.560
[Guest]: not just cost effectiveness,

02:28:32.560 --> 02:28:34.560
[Guest]: but governance and pedagogy, right?

02:28:34.560 --> 02:28:35.560
[Guest]: So it's a very concrete idea.

02:28:35.560 --> 02:28:36.560
[Guest]: So and what I try to do

02:28:36.560 --> 02:28:37.560
[Guest]: in my writing

02:28:37.560 --> 02:28:38.560
[Guest]: is kind of cover

02:28:38.560 --> 02:28:39.560
[Guest]: both the principles

02:28:39.560 --> 02:28:41.560
[Guest]: as well as very concrete ideas, right?

02:28:41.560 --> 02:28:42.560
[Guest]: Because abstract means

02:28:42.560 --> 02:28:43.560
[Guest]: sab kuch bol sakte hain.

02:28:43.560 --> 02:28:44.560
[Guest]: But it's like,

02:28:44.560 --> 02:28:46.560
[Guest]: now give me five implementable ideas

02:28:46.560 --> 02:28:47.560
[Guest]: that as a state education minister

02:28:47.560 --> 02:28:49.560
[Guest]: or secretary I can do, right?

02:28:49.560 --> 02:28:51.560
[Guest]: So the foundation literacy mission

02:28:51.560 --> 02:28:52.560
[Guest]: that I told you about

02:28:52.560 --> 02:28:53.560
[Guest]: is something a state can do.

02:28:53.560 --> 02:28:55.560
[Guest]: This is something a state can do, okay?

02:28:55.560 --> 02:28:56.560
[Guest]: So does that make sense

02:28:56.560 --> 02:28:57.560
[Guest]: before I move on

02:28:57.560 --> 02:28:58.560
[Amit Varma]: to my third big idea?

02:28:58.560 --> 02:28:59.560
[Amit Varma]: No, it makes a lot of sense.

02:28:59.560 --> 02:29:00.560
[Amit Varma]: I mean, a couple of reactions.

02:29:00.560 --> 02:29:01.560
[Amit Varma]: One, of course,

02:29:01.560 --> 02:29:02.560
[Amit Varma]: the point of education

02:29:02.560 --> 02:29:03.560
[Amit Varma]: is to educate children

02:29:03.560 --> 02:29:04.560
[Amit Varma]: not to employ teachers.

02:29:04.560 --> 02:29:05.560
[Amit Varma]: So that's something

02:29:05.560 --> 02:29:06.560
[Amit Varma]: we should keep in mind.

02:29:06.560 --> 02:29:07.560
[Amit Varma]: So I don't, you know,

02:29:07.560 --> 02:29:08.560
[Amit Varma]: what the outcomes

02:29:08.560 --> 02:29:09.560
[Amit Varma]: for teachers are

02:29:09.560 --> 02:29:10.560
[Amit Varma]: is kind of irrelevant for me,

02:29:10.560 --> 02:29:11.560
[Amit Varma]: though I can see why

02:29:11.560 --> 02:29:12.560
[Amit Varma]: in the political economy

02:29:12.560 --> 02:29:13.560
[Amit Varma]: the unions would matter.

02:29:13.560 --> 02:29:14.560
[Amit Varma]: In the same way

02:29:14.560 --> 02:29:15.560
[Amit Varma]: that the point of markets,

02:29:15.560 --> 02:29:16.560
[Amit Varma]: for example,

02:29:16.560 --> 02:29:17.560
[Amit Varma]: is not to protect local businesses

02:29:17.560 --> 02:29:18.560
[Amit Varma]: but to fulfill

02:29:18.560 --> 02:29:19.560
[Amit Varma]: the needs of customers.

02:29:19.560 --> 02:29:20.560
[Amit Varma]: And we often get

02:29:20.560 --> 02:29:21.560
[Amit Varma]: the wrong way around.

02:29:21.560 --> 02:29:22.560
[Amit Varma]: And for me,

02:29:22.560 --> 02:29:23.560
[Amit Varma]: the big aha moment

02:29:23.560 --> 02:29:24.560
[Amit Varma]: that you just provided

02:29:24.560 --> 02:29:25.560
[Amit Varma]: is when you, you know,

02:29:25.560 --> 02:29:26.560
[Amit Varma]: you referred to that study

02:29:26.560 --> 02:29:27.560
[Amit Varma]: about how, you know,

02:29:27.560 --> 02:29:28.560
[Amit Varma]: you'll get better outcomes

02:29:28.560 --> 02:29:29.560
[Amit Varma]: for health care

02:29:29.560 --> 02:29:30.560
[Amit Varma]: if sometimes,

02:29:30.560 --> 02:29:31.560
[Amit Varma]: if you build roads

02:29:31.560 --> 02:29:32.560
[Amit Varma]: rather than clinics.

02:29:32.560 --> 02:29:33.560
[Amit Varma]: And similarly,

02:29:33.560 --> 02:29:34.560
[Amit Varma]: you can get better outcomes

02:29:34.560 --> 02:29:35.560
[Amit Varma]: for primary education

02:29:35.560 --> 02:29:36.560
[Amit Varma]: if you hire buses

02:29:36.560 --> 02:29:37.560
[Amit Varma]: instead of building schools,

02:29:37.560 --> 02:29:38.560
[Amit Varma]: which is, you know,

02:29:38.560 --> 02:29:39.560
[Amit Varma]: such a phenomenal

02:29:39.560 --> 02:29:40.560
[Amit Varma]: and a very counterintuitive

02:29:40.560 --> 02:29:41.560
[Amit Varma]: way of thinking about it.

02:29:41.560 --> 02:29:42.560
[Amit Varma]: And I think, you know,

02:29:42.560 --> 02:29:43.560
[Amit Varma]: if local communities

02:29:43.560 --> 02:29:44.560
[Amit Varma]: are given all of these choices,

02:29:44.560 --> 02:29:45.560
[Amit Varma]: you will have a thousand flowers

02:29:45.560 --> 02:29:46.560
[Amit Varma]: blooming,

02:29:46.560 --> 02:29:47.560
[Amit Varma]: different experiments.

02:29:47.560 --> 02:29:48.560
[Amit Varma]: I mean, you know,

02:29:48.560 --> 02:29:49.560
[Amit Varma]: there's a limited set

02:29:49.560 --> 02:29:50.560
[Amit Varma]: of conventional ideas

02:29:50.560 --> 02:29:51.560
[Amit Varma]: on this that exists

02:29:51.560 --> 02:29:52.560
[Amit Varma]: within government.

02:29:52.560 --> 02:29:53.560
[Amit Varma]: Economists like you

02:29:53.560 --> 02:29:54.560
[Amit Varma]: bring in some more

02:29:54.560 --> 02:29:55.560
[Amit Varma]: like you just did,

02:29:55.560 --> 02:29:56.560
[Amit Varma]: but just open it out

02:29:56.560 --> 02:29:57.560
[Amit Varma]: to local communities

02:29:57.560 --> 02:29:58.560
[Amit Varma]: and I'm sure

02:29:58.560 --> 02:29:59.560
[Amit Varma]: there'll be stuff

02:29:59.560 --> 02:30:00.560
[Amit Varma]: that even you

02:30:00.560 --> 02:30:01.560
[Amit Varma]: couldn't have thought about.

02:30:01.560 --> 02:30:02.560
[Amit Varma]: So you have to kind of

02:30:02.560 --> 02:30:03.560
[Amit Varma]: enable that to happen.

02:30:03.560 --> 02:30:04.560
[Amit Varma]: I'll ask you to move on now.

02:30:04.560 --> 02:30:06.560
[Guest]: No, no, no, exactly.

02:30:06.560 --> 02:30:07.560
[Guest]: End of question.

02:30:07.560 --> 02:30:08.560
[Guest]: And so, but again,

02:30:08.560 --> 02:30:09.560
[Guest]: I mean, the challenge,

02:30:09.560 --> 02:30:10.560
[Guest]: and again,

02:30:10.560 --> 02:30:11.560
[Guest]: which is why I think

02:30:11.560 --> 02:30:12.560
[Guest]: we definitely need

02:30:12.560 --> 02:30:13.560
[Guest]: an episode in federalism

02:30:13.560 --> 02:30:14.560
[Guest]: is because the entire

02:30:14.560 --> 02:30:15.560
[Guest]: culture in Indian government

02:30:15.560 --> 02:30:16.560
[Guest]: is one of kind of

02:30:16.560 --> 02:30:17.560
[Guest]: lack of trust, right?

02:30:17.560 --> 02:30:18.560
[Guest]: So one of the reasons

02:30:18.560 --> 02:30:19.560
[Guest]: you don't move the money down

02:30:19.560 --> 02:30:20.560
[Guest]: is you'll say,

02:30:20.560 --> 02:30:21.560
[Guest]: it'll get siphoned away

02:30:21.560 --> 02:30:22.560
[Guest]: by the local political elites, right?

02:30:22.560 --> 02:30:23.560
[Guest]: So, which is why

02:30:23.560 --> 02:30:24.560
[Guest]: you need to combine

02:30:24.560 --> 02:30:25.560
[Guest]: that autonomy and process

02:30:25.560 --> 02:30:26.560
[Guest]: with accountability and outcomes.

02:30:26.560 --> 02:30:27.560
[Guest]: And so there is this

02:30:27.560 --> 02:30:28.560
[Guest]: very delicate

02:30:28.560 --> 02:30:29.560
[Guest]: federal architecture, right?

02:30:29.560 --> 02:30:30.560
[Guest]: You know, that is,

02:30:30.560 --> 02:30:31.560
[Guest]: should be discussed,

02:30:31.560 --> 02:30:32.560
[Guest]: you know, at length

02:30:32.560 --> 02:30:33.560
[Guest]: in a separate,

02:30:33.560 --> 02:30:34.560
[Guest]: separate panel.

02:30:34.560 --> 02:30:35.560
[Guest]: So I think the third idea,

02:30:35.560 --> 02:30:36.560
[Guest]: and frankly,

02:30:36.560 --> 02:30:37.560
[Guest]: if tomorrow,

02:30:37.560 --> 02:30:38.560
[Guest]: if I was an education minister,

02:30:38.560 --> 02:30:39.560
[Guest]: this is the single

02:30:39.560 --> 02:30:40.560
[Guest]: most important thing

02:30:40.560 --> 02:30:41.560
[Guest]: I would do, okay?

02:30:41.560 --> 02:30:42.560
[Guest]: And this is something

02:30:42.560 --> 02:30:43.560
[Guest]: that straddles

02:30:43.560 --> 02:30:44.560
[Guest]: a whole range

02:30:44.560 --> 02:30:45.560
[Guest]: of service delivery sectors.

02:30:45.560 --> 02:30:46.560
[Guest]: And it basically

02:30:46.560 --> 02:30:47.560
[Guest]: has to do

02:30:47.560 --> 02:30:48.560
[Guest]: with the following

02:30:48.560 --> 02:30:49.560
[Guest]: simple idea, okay?

02:30:49.560 --> 02:30:50.560
[Guest]: That one of the foundational

02:30:50.560 --> 02:30:51.560
[Guest]: aspects of weak state

02:30:51.560 --> 02:30:52.560
[Guest]: capacity in India

02:30:52.560 --> 02:30:53.560
[Guest]: is we don't have

02:30:53.560 --> 02:30:54.560
[Guest]: enough frontline employees, okay?

02:30:54.560 --> 02:30:55.560
[Guest]: We are understaffed

02:30:55.560 --> 02:30:56.560
[Guest]: in education,

02:30:56.560 --> 02:30:57.560
[Guest]: we're understaffed in police,

02:30:57.560 --> 02:30:58.560
[Guest]: we're understaffed in health,

02:30:58.560 --> 02:30:59.560
[Guest]: we're understaffed in

02:30:59.560 --> 02:31:00.560
[Guest]: Anganwadis,

02:31:00.560 --> 02:31:01.560
[Guest]: but the reason you're understaffed

02:31:01.560 --> 02:31:02.560
[Guest]: is because salaries

02:31:02.560 --> 02:31:03.560
[Guest]: is you get like 200,

02:31:03.560 --> 02:31:04.560
[Guest]: 300 applicants

02:31:04.560 --> 02:31:05.560
[Guest]: for every government job, right?

02:31:05.560 --> 02:31:06.560
[Guest]: So Econ 101

02:31:06.560 --> 02:31:07.560
[Guest]: will tell you,

02:31:07.560 --> 02:31:08.560
[Guest]: like you lower the wage

02:31:08.560 --> 02:31:09.560
[Guest]: and increase the quantity, right?

02:31:09.560 --> 02:31:10.560
[Guest]: And we don't do that.

02:31:10.560 --> 02:31:11.560
[Guest]: Now,

02:31:11.560 --> 02:31:12.560
[Guest]: it's not enough

02:31:12.560 --> 02:31:13.560
[Guest]: to just say that

02:31:13.560 --> 02:31:14.560
[Guest]: the salaries are too high

